The Coral was able to do it’s default detection OK, so we moved to install the pre-trained neural net pathways on our Limelight. This resulted in the LL getting into a ‘hard running’ state (fan running at full speed) where it flashed its LEDs once about every 10 sec and seemed to be unresponsive. After about 10 minutes, I powered off, unplugged the Coral and tried booting with just the LL, but it was still in that state. I opted to re-flash the LL to make a second attempt later. Any advice on what we should do differently? It seemed pretty straight forward, so not sure if we should have just been more patient with it. The directions don’t give any indication of what to expect when configuring this, or any troubleshooting.
